<p itemprop="description">A data analyst applies analytical techniques to extract insights from data, supporting evidence-based decision making across the organisation. They work independently on analytical projects and communicate findings to stakeholders.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Conduct comprehensive data analysis to answer complex business questions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design and create reports, dashboards, and visualisations for stakeholders</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Apply statistical methods and analytical techniques to identify trends and patterns</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with business users to understand analytical requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Present findings and recommendations to non-technical audiences</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure data quality and integrity in analytical outputs</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support policy development and operational improvement through data insights</li>
    </ul>
</section>

